        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Now this is a guide on how to trigger the AC in Sro and i know a lot of people reading this are going to say its bullsh!t but its not, my friend did this with a few people one night and got 3 rings in 4 EQ nights and i told someone else about it and they got 2 rings in a few hours and i've got 1 spare ring this way so it does work.

Before i go in to details its best to have a few people for it because the AC can spawn in 3 places and it involves clearing the desert of all undead mobs.

Using this method you can get 1 AC every 45 mins (EQ day) Remember though he is still a random/rare spawn so this isn't the only way to make him spawn but as far as i know it is the most reliable.

1. At 10pm game time start clearing the desert area of undead and only undead, kill everything undead, mummy's, ghouls dry bones etc. but DO NOT kill the undead mob in the tower (this is the trigger) Also kill any rares like SG's, Terrorantula etc.

2. By 3am game time if you've done it properly there should be no undead up at all, if there is a single undead mob in the desert it will not work. The idea here is that by killing all the undead hopefully live things like spiders will spawn in there spot and by the time it gets to 3am there is not a single undead mob up EXCEPT for the one in the tower.

3. At 3am kill the undead mob in the tower and if you have done it correctly the AC should pop straight away in 1 of its 3 spawn spots.

Side Note: Its best if your group is the only group of people after the AC, if other people there doing the old kill everything they see tactic they will screw it up for you.
One night i was there from 10pm till 1am and i was the only person in the zone then some punk zones in and starts killing all the spiders and guess what...no AC at 3am.



*I'll re read this later and make any needed changes but i'm running short on time so its going up like it is now but i think thats all correct.

----------------------
-Barben-             
52 Gnome Nerfomancer 
Karana               
----------------------



Edited by - Barben on 03/13/2001  01:00:30
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        

